}}As of the 2020 census, there were 219 people, 107 housing units, and 49 families in the CDP. The racial makeup was 91.3% [[White Americans|White]], 0.9% [[African Americans|African American]], and 7.8% from [[Multiracial Americans|two or more races]]. 0.9% of the population were of [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] origin.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile?g=160XX00US2111188 |access-date=2023-06-21 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry of the CDP was 59.8% [[Americans|American]], and 5.9% [[Portuguese Americans|Portuguese]].<ref name=":0" />

The median age was 62.6 years old. A total of 32.4% of the population were 65 or older, with 5.9% between 65 and, 0.0% between 75 and 84, and 26.5% were 85 or older. A total of 4.9% of the population were between the ages of 5 and 14.<ref name=":0" />

A total of 26.5% of the population were in poverty. A total of 81.8% of people over 65 were in poverty.<ref name=":0" />{{clear left}}

